{"TERTIAL":[{"def":"Same as Tertiary.","pos":""}],"TERTIAN":[{"def":"Occurring every third day; as, a tertian fever.","pos":""}],"TERTIARY":[{"def":"Possessing some quality in the third degree; having been subjected to the substitution of three atoms or radicals; as, a tertiary alcohol, amine, or salt.","pos":""},{"def":"Later than, or subsequent to, the Secondary.","pos":""}],"TERTIATE":[{"def":"To examine, as the thickness of the metal at the muzzle of a gun; or, in general, to examine the thickness of, as ordnance, in order to ascertain its strength.","pos":""}],"TERTIUM QUID":[{"def":"A third somewhat; something mediating, or regarded as being, between two diverse or incompatible substances, natures, or positions.","pos":""}]}